# 🚀 MCP SDK Commit Message Template
# =====================================
#
# 📋 Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#           |
#           └─> 📝 <body>
#           |
#           └─> 🔗 <footer>
#
# =====================================
# 🎯 COMMIT TYPES (choose one)
# =====================================
#
# ✨ feat:     🌟 New feature for the user
# 🐛 fix:      🔧 Bug fix for the user
# 📚 docs:     📖 Documentation changes
# 🎨 style:    🎭 Formatting, missing semi-colons, etc (no code change)
# ♻️ refactor: 🔄 Refactoring production code
# 🧪 test:     ⚗️ Adding tests, refactoring test (no production code change)
# 🔧 chore:    🛠️ Updating build tasks, package configs (no production code change)
# ⚡ perf:     ⚡ Performance improvements
# 💥 breaking: 💣 Breaking changes
# 🔒 security: 🛡️ Security fixes
# 🚀 build:    🏗️ Build system changes
# 📦 deps:     📦 Dependency updates
# 🔍 revert:   ↩️ Reverting previous changes
# ✅ ci:       🔄 CI/CD related changes
# 🔧 config:   ⚙️ Configuration changes
#
# =====================================
# 🌍 SCOPE AREAS (choose relevant ones)
# =====================================
#
# 🔧 core:       Core MCP functionality
# 🤖 agents:     Agent management & lifecycle
# 🔌 plugins:    Plugin system & architecture
# 🔐 auth:       Authentication & authorization
# 🗺️ geospatial: Geospatial features & mapping
# 🍄 myceloom:   Myceloom protocol implementation
# 📖 docs:       Documentation & guides
# 🧪 tests:      Test infrastructure & suites
# 🏗️ build:      Build & deployment systems
# 🌐 api:        API endpoints & routes
# 💾 data:       Data models & storage
# 🔄 ci:         CI/CD pipelines & automation
# 📊 monitoring: Observability & metrics
# 🌍 i18n:       Internationalization
# 🎯 cli:        Command-line interface
# 📱 client:     Client libraries & SDKs
# 🔄 sync:       Data synchronization
# 🎭 ui:         User interface components
# 🔍 search:     Search functionality
# 📈 analytics:  Analytics & reporting
# 🌐 network:    Network & communication
# 🔧 tools:      Development tools & utilities
# 🧮 math:       Mathematical operations
# 🎨 themes:     UI themes & styling
# 🔊 audio:      Audio processing
# 🎬 video:      Video processing
# 📷 images:     Image processing
# 📝 forms:      Form handling & validation
# 🗂️ files:      File management
# 📧 email:      Email functionality
# 💬 chat:       Chat & messaging
# 📅 calendar:   Calendar & scheduling
# 📍 location:   Location services
# 🌡️ sensors:    Sensor data & IoT
# 🎮 gaming:     Gaming features
# 🎵 music:      Music functionality
# 📰 news:       News & feeds
# 🛒 ecommerce:  E-commerce features
# 📦 inventory:  Inventory management
# 💰 payments:   Payment processing
# 📊 charts:     Charts & visualization
# 🗃️ database:  Database operations
# 🌐 webhooks:   Webhook handling
# 📱 mobile:     Mobile-specific features
# 🖥️ desktop:   Desktop-specific features
#
# =====================================
# 💡 WRITING GUIDELINES
# =====================================
#
# 📌 Subject:
#   • Use imperative tense ("Add" not "Added" or "Adds")
#   • Keep it under 50 characters when possible
#   • Start with a verb that describes the change
#   • Add relevant emoji to enhance visual appeal
#   • Capitalize the first letter
#
# 📝 Body:
#   • Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
#   • Include context for future contributors
#   • Reference technical decisions made
#   • Mention performance impacts if relevant
#   • Keep lines under 72 characters
#
# 🔗 Footer:
#   • Closes: #issue-number
#   • BREAKING CHANGE: description
#   • Co-authored-by: Name <email>
#   • References: related issues or PRs
#
# =====================================
# 🌟 EXAMPLE TEMPLATES
# =====================================
#
# ✨ feat(agents): 🤖 Add agent lifecycle management
# 📝
#   Implement comprehensive agent lifecycle including initialization,
#   execution, monitoring, and graceful shutdown. This enables proper
#   resource management and error handling across the MCP ecosystem.
#
#   Closes: #123
#   Co-authored-by: Jane Doe <jane@example.com>
#
# 🐛 fix(auth): 🔐 Resolve JWT token validation issue
# 📝
#   Fix token expiration validation that was causing authentication
#   failures for long-running sessions. Updated validation logic to
#   properly handle edge cases with timezone differences.
#
#   Fixes: #456
#
# 🚀 Get started! Your commit tells the story of our collective progress.
